Package: gsed
Version: 4.1.4
Revision: 1
License: GPL
Maintainer: Lars Rosengreen <lars@margay.org>
Description: GNU stream editor

Depends: libiconv, gettext
BuildDepends: gettext-dev, gettext-bin, gettext-tools, libiconv-dev
Conflicts: sed, ssed

Source: mirror:gnu:sed/sed-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 2a62ceadcb571d2dac006f81df5ddb48
SourceDirectory: sed-%v

ConfigureParams: --with-libiconv-prefix=%p --mandir=%p/share/man --infodir=%p/share/info --program-prefix=g
InstallScript: <<
 make install DESTDIR=%d
 mv %i/share/info/sed.info %i/share/info/gsed.info
 mkdir -p %i/share/doc/%n
 mv %i/share/doc/sed.html %i/share/doc/%n/sed.html
<<
DocFiles: README COPYING AUTHORS BUGS NEWS THANKS
InfoDocs: gsed.info

DescDetail: <<
sed is a text stream editor that is commonly used to process text from
shell scripts and makefiles. 
<<

DescPackaging: <<
Previous versions by Christoph Pfisterer. and Sylvain Cuaz

No update-alternatives.  IMO, using it here would be an invitiation for
future headaches.  sed should always be BSD sed.
<<

DescUsage: <<
The executable installs as "%p/bin/gsed"
<<

Homepage: http://www.gnu.org/software/sed/sed.html
